parameters: \n< Serena >Hm...
\n< Serena >...So that's an orc...

\n< Serena >Avoid a direct confrontation, huh. I see, it
certainly has enough power to make you say that.

\n< Serena >If we leave it alone, will those monsters swarm
into the town?

\n< Serena >In that case, we have no choice but to exterminate
them here!

\n< Serena >Phew... It was quite tough, but it seems to be
settled.
\n< Serena >Anyway, it's settled. Let's go back and report.

\n< Guild Master >You're back, young one. It seems like you handled
it well.
\n< Serena >Yes, I defeated two orcs as expected.
\n< Guild Master >Oh, then listen...
\n< Serena >....
\n< Guild Master >What? Don't tell me it was you...

\n< Serena >Well, since I've defeated them, there shouldn't be
any problems.
\n< Guild Master >Hey hey, you can't confirm the facts, can you?

\n< Serena >In that case, it would be best to have someone
confirm it. Since there is no need for a reward
this time, we can cover the expenses with that.

\n< Guild Master >...Well, that's the only option, so we'll handle
it like that this time too. Listen, young one,
work is something that should be done according to
the rules.

\n< Guild Master >No matter how you try to fill in the gaps with
exceptions, the burden will still fall somewhere.

\n< Guild Master >Once you take on a job, young one, you're a
professional. Complete the requests you receive
and make sure to receive your proper reward.
\n< Serena >I see. That makes sense.
\n< Serena >But I don't like what I don't like.

\n< Guild Master >Geez... deducting the labor fee from the reward...
this is the only amount for this time.

\n< Serena >Alright, with this, there are \V[2501] more cases
to go.
"  The orcs were strong, but crumbled before my sonic fist."
"  Let's go back to the inn."

\n< Serena >E-Erika-sama...
\n< Erika >Alright, alright, Serena, are you okay?
\n< Erika >You did well. Leave the rest to me!
\n< Erika >Drashea!
\n< Erika >Alright, here we go.
\n< Serena >？
\n< Erika >Here we go.
\n< Serena >What is it?
\n< Erika >No, I wonder if I want to hug you...
\n< Serena >It's fine.

\n< Erika >Is it okay for you to cry your heart out on my
chest? I'll comfort you and say there, there.
\n< Serena >It's fine... but I am grateful.

\n< Serena >Honestly, I was prepared to die. Even though I
can't die in a place like this.
\n< Serena >Thank you, Erika-sama. You saved me... truly.
\n< Erika >Ehehe.

\n< Erika >Well, I've made my fair share of mistakes too. And
every time, I've been helped by someone in a
similar way.

\n< Erika >If Serena is grateful for what happened today,
then if she ever sees someone in the same
profession going through a similar experience, she
should help them out.
\n< Serena >Understood. I will definitely do that.
\n< Erika >Alright then, shall we go home?

\n< Serena >Before that, I want to stop by the water source.
Is that okay?

\n< Serena >Something... like venom was poured on me... It's a
sticky white liquid.
\n< Erika >Huh?

\n< Serena >It got into my mouth a little... It doesn't seem
to have an immediate effect though...
\n< Erika >Ah, ah, ahhhhh.
\n< Serena >？

\n< Erika >No, yeah, that's right. It's probably better to
wash it off.
\n< Erika >It's not poison, but it's dirty, so wipe it off.

\n< Serena >I feel like I'm being treated like a child after
all...
\n< Guild Master >Alright, good work. This is your reward.

\n< Serena >...No, haven't you heard the report? Erika-sama
assisted this time. I was just helped. I want this
reward to be given to Erika-sama.

\n< Guild Master >From the guild's perspective, it doesn't really
matter. Either way, the request has been
completed. So, I will give you the reward. As for
how to divide that reward, it's up to you guys to
decide.
\n< Serena >Um, that is...

\n< Guild Master >It's not really a rare story for subcontractors
and sub-subcontractors in a request. In other
words, the adventurer's guild itself is like a
huge subcontractor.

\n< Guild Master >So as long as the result is as requested, it
doesn't really matter how the process went from
the guild's perspective.

\n< Guild Master >Well, even if it's said like that, Erika's share
will probably be rejected, you know.

\n< Guild Master >Ah, I'll say this as a reminder, but it's not a
good attitude for adventurers. In the end,
settling things with money is the smoothest way to
resolve things.

\n< Guild Master >But... why not treat her to a drink or something?
That's what she would appreciate the most.
\n< Serena >...I understand.
\n< Serena >Thank you, Master.
\n< Guild Master >Alright.
\n< Serena >...So, this is the last \V[2501] request.
"I lost to an orc."
"  What would have happened if Lady Erika were not here...?"
"  It would be good to wash my body at the hot springs."
